Hi,

I'm thinking about trying for four techs next semester (EE16B, CS160, EE120, CS188) and given that two of these are mostly hw and the other two have projects (from what I hear are pretty straightforward and simple) I want to find a breadth I could take that wouldn't have much for me to do except simple hw and exams. Has anyone taken a course like this that fulfills the International Breadth? Also, was my intel on the difficulty of these techs accurate?
history.subject: International Breath with little to no work (exception of midterms and final)
